{
  "id": "helix-turbo-cache",
  "title": "Optimize turbo.json cache configuration for test results and CEM artifacts",
  "category": "automation",
  "description": "The current `turbo.json` may not be fully caching all build and test outputs. Optimize the configuration to maximize cache hits in CI and local development.\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Read the current `turbo.json` configuration\n2. Audit the pipeline tasks: `build`, `test`, `lint`, `type-check`, `cem`, `clean`\n3. Add `outputs` to `test` task (test results JSON at `packages/hx-library/.cache/test-results.json`)\n4. Add `outputs` to `cem` task (`custom-elements.json` in each package)\n5. Ensure `build` task outputs include `dist/**` for all packages\n6. Add `env` arrays to tasks that depend on environment variables\n7. Verify the `dev` task is not cached (should always run)\n8. Verify `clean` task has `cache: false`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `turbo.json` has explicit `outputs` for build, test, and cem tasks\n- Second run of `turbo build` shows `>>> FULL TURBO` cache hit\n- `turbo test` caches test results correctly\n- No regressions in build or test behavior",
